[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 10     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m <!-- What is the problem? What change do you believe will improve the target agent? Why? -->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The agent wastes 5-10 steps per task trying to `import apis` (via `import apis`, `from appworld import apis`, `import appworld.apis`, etc.) because the system prompt does not tell it that `apis` is a pre-injected global variable requiring no import. Adding an explicit "CRITICAL: `apis` is a pre-injected global variable. Do NOT import it." instruction to the system prompt will eliminate these wasted steps, allowing the agent to spend its step budget on actual task work, fixing the "step exhaustion due to import errors" failure class.
